Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, trim the @Green Beans{80%g} and cut into thirds.

Next, stir the green beans into the chicken.

Stir-fry, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @Teriyaki Sauce{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Remove from the heat.
> IMPORTANT: Cook so it's no longer pink in the middle.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash of @water{splash} if needed.

Fluff up the rice and top with the teriyaki chicken.

Sprinkle over the @Chilli Flakes{1%pinch} and @Crispy Onions{1%sachet}.

> Add less chilli flakes if you'd prefer things milder.

Enjoy!